Time Warner’s ‘Hangover’ Sequel Has $30 Million in Friday Sales

-- B y   D a n   H a r t
-- 
2011-05-28T15:49:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-28/time-warner-s-hangover-sequel-is-poised-for-weekend-sales-of-80-million.html
Time Warner Inc. (TWX) ’s “Hangover: Part
II” had $30 million in receipts yesterday, putting the sequel
on track to post weekend sales of about $80 million,
Hollywood.com Box Office said today in an e-mailed statement.  The film may post sales of as much as $100 million for the
four-day Memorial Day holiday weekend, Hollywood.com said. The
movie is showing in 3,615 theaters.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Dan Hart  at 
 dahart@bloomberg.net  